    "body": "Ok, here's what I *think* happened, please correct me if wrong:\r\n\r\n- The difference in `sstore` implementation led to two different chains.\r\n- The majority of peers seem to be parity at the moment, but there are a couple geth peers\r\n- So, my geth node kept choosing a parity peer when trying to sync\r\n- Which led to the blocks being rejected during downloading\r\n- However, since this is a consensus bug and not an explicit fork, there's no way for geth to know which `highestBlock` value is valid before downloading and verifying, so it has to report the highestBlock seen over all.",
